cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper deals with resource allocation in millimeterWave wireless networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of distributed algorithms and the focus on control and relaying could also place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
